pageContext.claim: “We got a lot -- trade. Japan has already contacted us; they came last week. Don't forget -- Japan would not deal with Obama. He wouldn't deal with President Obama. They wouldn't deal. They said, "No, we're not going to talk trade." Me? They're calling up.”
pageContext.analysis: Japan dealt extensively with the Obama administration. Both President Obama and Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe championed the Trans-Pacific Partnership, a multinational trade deal that Trump terminated.
